OL,4,CJohnson
OL,6,FIn the run up to D-Day she served as a
OL,7,Fconvoy driver, taking vehicles to
OL,8,FChannel ports where preparations were
OL,9,Funderway to load them onto ships ahead
OL,10,Fof the landings.
OL,12,FShe said: "It was hard work because
OL,13,Fyou had no assistance, especially the
OL,14,Fhandbrake which was on a ratchet, you
OL,15,Fhad to pull it up.
OL,17,F"So every morning you had to check
OL,18,Feverything. It took time to get it on
OL,19,Fthe road."
